<p itemprop="description">A senior interaction designer leads user experience design for complex digital programmes and services. They mentor junior designers, establish design standards, and drive user-centred design practices while ensuring accessibility and inclusive design principles are embedded throughout the design process.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead interaction design for complex, multi-service digital programmes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Develop comprehensive design systems and interaction patterns</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Mentor and develop junior interaction designers and UX capability</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish interaction design standards and best practices</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead cross-functional collaboration to embed user-centred thinking</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation in interaction design tools, techniques, and methodologies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide expert guidance on complex accessibility and usability challenges</li>
    </ul>
</section>

